# COVID-19 Data Analysis

This project focuses on analyzing global COVID-19 data to understand trends in confirmed cases, deaths, and recoveries using Python.  
The analysis includes data preprocessing, aggregation, and visualization of real-world data.

---

## Project Overview
The objective of this project is to explore COVID-19 trends across different countries and time periods through data analysis and visualization techniques.

Key highlights:
- Global trend analysis
- Country-wise comparison
- Visual representation of COVID-19 impact

---

## Dataset Information
The dataset used for this project is sourced from Kaggle:

ðŸ”— **COVID-19 Dataset (Kaggle):**  
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/maheshashwin/covid19-dataset

Due to GitHubâ€™s file size limitations (files larger than 25 MB), the dataset is **not included** in this repository.

### How to use the dataset
1. Visit the Kaggle link above  
2. Download the dataset (CSV file)  
3. Place the CSV file in this project folder  
4. Run the Python script to perform the analysis  

---

## Tools & Technologies
- Python  
- Pandas  
- Matplotlib  

---

## Output
- Line graphs showing global COVID-19 trends  
- Bar charts comparing country-wise cases and deaths  

---

## Learning Outcomes
- Handling large real-world datasets  
- Data cleaning and preprocessing  
- Data visualization using Python  
- Extracting insights from data  

